(194, 3, 28, 'message', 'Re: (A d v) Available premises to open another F&B outlet/branch in Singapore\r\n\r\n\r\nTo: Whom It may concern:\r\n\r\nPlease send the following information to your business manager for Singapore.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nHui Kee\r\n****************\r\n\r\nHi There,\r\n\r\nI''m a real estate/property agent in Singapore.  Are you looking to expand your business in F&B?  Please find below some restaurant/takeaway spaces available for rent.  Please do feel free to contact me for more info / no-obligations viewing.  Refer your friend and receive a thank-you referral fee on successful rental of the place.\r\n\r\nIf you know of anybody who is looking to pre-terminate any lease, please also do not hesitate to contact me, as I may have the right person to take over your friend''s lease.\r\n\r\nThank you for your attention.\r\n\r\nLook forward to hearing from you!\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nHui Kee\r\n\r\nChua Hui Kee\r\nMobile: 65 90401628\r\nCEA Reg No: R004952D\r\nDreamloft Properties Pte Ltd, Ltd, Singapore\r\nLicense No. L30096011\r\n(Part of Remax)\r\n\r\n*************************************\r\n\r\n(1) Orchard Road\r\n2,400 sq ft asking for $50k per month negotiable Isetan Scotts at Shaw House in Orchard Road has a unit for rent.  The unit is about 2,400 sq ft asking for about $50k per month negotiable.  Rental is negotiable.  The earliest it is available at the end of October, the exact date is to be confirmed.  There is no percentage of sales component, which is very rare for Orchard Road.\r\n\r\nThis is a rarely available unit at Isetan Scotts, and your company can tap on both local customers and Japanese customers (who shop at Isetan on a regular basis).  Your F&B neighbours include Tonkichi  Restaurant, Dome Café, TCC, and Restaurant Hoshigaoka.  At the same time, you can tap on the large number of movie-goers at Shaw''s flapship cinema in Singapore, Lido Cineplex which is located on the uppermost floor above the Isetan department store.\r\n\r\nIsetan Scotts is located at 350 Orchard Road.  It is prominently located at the intersection of Orchard Road and Scotts Road.  Isetan Scotts is frequented by Japanese expatriates living in Singapore and Singapore shoppers.  It is wildly popular among Singaporean customers due to its wide range, reasonable prices and excellent customer service, thus offering a truly one-stop shopping experience that is embraced by Singaporeans.  It operates a membership club known as Isetan members and its private sales are very popular amongst local Singaporeans. Isetan Scotts occupy the first five floors.  Above Isetan is Shaw''s flagship Cineplex in Singapore.  Shaw operates 7 cinemas in Singapore and Shaw Theatres Lido is the largest and arguably the most central (besides Bugis Junction) in Singapore.  Shaw Lido Cineplex reopened its door in May\r\n2011  after a major upgrade and revamp.\r\n\r\n(2) Orchard Road\r\nAbout 3.500 sqft View to offer\r\nThe unit currently occupied by Wendy''s (fast food) at Liat Towers is for rent.  Liat Towers is next to Wheelock Place in Orchard Road.\r\n\r\nThe size is about 3,500 sqft on a view-to-offer basis.  This is a very crowded area in Orchard Road, directly opposite Isetan Scotts.  It also stands at the junction of Orchard Road and Scotts Road.\r\n\r\nWhat you offer will be able to attract both locals and tourists.\r\n\r\nI would suggest a $20 per sq ft bid to put yourself in a good position.\r\n\r\n(2) Orchard Road/Dhoby Ghaut\r\nRestaurant space at SMU (Singapore Management University) for Rent\r\nAsking about $18k for 1,800 sqft\r\nCapitalise on students from SMU and other private schools, office professionals and tourists.\r\nGreat opportunity for branding as street-level\r\nNear Plaza by the Park, Singapore Art Museum, National Museum.\r\n\r\n(3) Raffles Place\r\n320 sq ft shop with exhaust asking for $8,000 negotiable\r\nTap on unbelievable office crowds from nearby office buildings including Far East Square, Capital Square, Samsung Hub, Prudential Towers.\r\nNo gas cooking allowed.\r\n\r\n(4) Raffles Place\r\nF&B Space of about 800sqft asking for about $16,000\r\n800sqft rarely available café space for rent at Robinson Road in Raffles Place, asking rent is about $16,000 ($20 per sqft).  Street level, prominent visibility.\r\n\r\n(5) Raffles Place - Far East Square\r\nF&B Space of about 2,250 sqft for rent at about $25,000 negotiable.  Tap on unbelievable office crowds from nearby office buildings including  Capital Square, Samsung Hub, Prudential Towers.\r\n\r\n(7) Shenton Way\r\nRestaurant Space for takeover.\r\nNo takeover fee.  (All equipment will be removed).\r\nTap on office crowd in Tanjong Pagar area (neighbouring buildings include International Plaza, MAS Building, etc.)\r\nAbout 1,840 sqft.\r\nCurrent rent is about $24k.\r\n\r\n(8) Anson Road/Shenton Way\r\nF&B Space for rent.\r\nAvailable in April 2015.\r\nGreat frontage.\r\nAbout 1,500 sqft.\r\nCurrent rent is about $24k + 1% GTO negotiable.\r\nNo exhaust.\r\n\r\n(9) Fullerton One\r\nRestaurant Space of 8,200 sq ft asking for $17 per sq ft (About $140k)\r\nnegotiable  or 15% of GTO, whichever is higher.\r\nLandlord is open to renting only 4,000 sqft (not less).\r\nAvailable in February/March 2015.\r\n\r\n(10) Fullerton Waterhouse\r\nRestaurant Space of about 2,900 sqft, consisting of 2,070 sqft indoors and 830 sqft outdoors.\r\nAsking for about $51k negotiable or 15% of GTO, whichever is higher.\r\nExcellent view of the Marina area.\r\n\r\n(11) Holland Village 2-storey shophouse.\r\nAbout 3,400 sqft in total size, also on a view-to-offer basis.\r\nHolland Village is a well-known entertainment & dining place for both locals & expatriates in Singapore.\r\nInstructed to present all offers.\r\nI would think that $12 to $15 per sq ft is the reasonable rent.\r\n\r\n(12) Robertson Quay area\r\nAbout 950 sqft café space for rent\r\nNo exhaust\r\nRent is about $12,300 +1% GTO.\r\n\r\n(13) UE Square\r\nAbout 1,760 sqft F&B space for rent\r\nNo exhaust\r\nRent is about $17,650.\r\n\r\n(14) Novena – United Square Shopping Mall\r\nKiosk for rent\r\nAbout 400 sqft asking for about $10,600+2% GTO.\r\nBenefit from (i) families, (ii) children attending tuition classes at shopping mall and (iii) office professionals from the attached 30-storey office building.\r\n\r\n(15) Mediapolis & Biopolis at Buona Vista\r\n1 unit  of about 2,100 sqft available asking for $5.50 per sq ft.  1 unit of 2,500 sqft asking for $3.72 per sqft.\r\nNeighbours include Revolution Coffee, Hoopla Coffee and Kitchen, Subway, Curbside Cafe & Wine Bar, and others.\r\nGain access to office workers in the media, biotechnology cluster.\r\nLandlord prefers Asian cuisines for the Mediapolis units.\r\n\r\n(16) Science Parks\r\n1 unit of about 1,470 sq ft at Science Hub Building and 1 unit of about 660 sqft at Alpha Building asking for $5.50 per sq ft. Tap on professionals working in the Science Parks.\r\n\r\n(17) JCube\r\nDine-in available for takeover/rent.\r\nAbout 760 sq ft at rental of about $12,400.\r\nAsking takeover fee is $40k for all quipment/furniture, except personal items/decoration pieces.\r\n\r\n(18)  F&B Space available for takeover opposite City Square Mall.\r\nWell-renovated restaurant in shophouse\r\n4,500 sqft, current rent is $25,000\r\nAsking for takeover fee of $200,000.\r\n\r\n'),
